All Classes

  • Class Description
    ColorDetectionController
    The primary class for handling color detection related tasks.
    Display
    This class is used to display the content of the odometer variables (x, y, theta).
    HookController
    This class contains the method controlling the movement of the hook by acting on the EV3 motor attached to it.
    LightSensorController
    Provides methods which helps with light localization and light intensity detection.
    Main
    The main driver class for the lab.
    MainController
    The Main thread for running the main program and allow user to perform different task based on the initial selection screen.
    Navigation
    The main class for performing movement with the motors and navigate to desire position based on the current location.
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) position.
    PathFinder
    The class help the main program determine the next course of action based on the current location.
    PathFinder.Grid
    Enumeration for the status of the grid.
    Point
    s Represents a coordinate point on the competition map grid.
    Region
    Represents a region on the competition map grid, delimited by its lower-left and upper-right corners (inclusive).
    Resources
    This class is used to define static resources in one place for easy access and to avoid cluttering the rest of the codebase.
    UltraSonicController  
    WifiConnection
    This class handles the acquisition of the Wi-Fi parameters from the server.
